entry.tran: 不再做(…)的;(同…)不再打交道的;(对…)不再感兴趣的
entry.def: Someone who is finished with something is no longer doing it or dealing with it or is no longer interested in it.

example.ex: One suspects he will be finished with boxing.
example.tran: 人们猜想他不会再打拳了。

entry.tran: 不复存在的;不再发生的
entry.def: Something that is finished no longer exists or is no longer happening.

example.ex: I go back on the dole when the shooting season's finished.
example.tran: 狩猎季节过后，我又重靠领取救济金过活。

entry.tran: 垮台的;完蛋的;失势的;失效的
entry.def: Someone or something that is finished is no longer important, powerful, or effective.

example.ex: Her power over me is finished...
He confessed: 'I thought I was finished.'
example.tran: 他承认道：“我以为自己已经完了。”

entry.tran: (以某种方式的外观或装饰)最后呈现的
entry.def: Something that is finished or finished off in a particular way has been given a particular appearance or decoration.

example.ex: The dining room is finished in deep red...
Each dress is beautifully finished off with piped seams and fitted underskirts.
example.tran: 每件连衣裙最后线缝都滚了边，并且加上了合身的衬裙，看起来非常漂亮。

means.word_mean: 1. (of materials or goods) brought to the desired final state;
2. ended or brought to an end;
3. (of skills or the products of skills) brought to or having the greatest excellence; perfected;

sentences.sentence: "a dazzling and finished piece of writing"

means.word_mean: 4. having a surface coating or finish applied;

sentences.sentence: "the finished bookcase costs much more than the unfinished ones"
"after the revolution the aristocracy was finished"
"the unsuccessful run for office left him ruined politically and economically"
